Compound.comment: The most abundant form of the phosphate ion at pH 7.3 is hydrogenphosphate. To simplify the presentation of reactions taking place at physiological pH, MetaCyc does not distinguish between the two forms, and uses the name "phosphate" even though the structure shown is that of hydrogenphosphate.
